COMPONENT NAME: LKM Oracle BI to SQL
AUTHOR: Oracle
DESCRIPTION - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from any Oracle BI physical layer to any ISO-92 compliant target database. - Uses ODI Agent to read selected data from the Oracle BI server physical layer and write the result into the target temporary table created dynamically.
REQUIREMENTS - Requires a Oracle BI data server with the folowwing JDBC property: NQ_SESSION.SELECTPHYSICAL = yes
BASIC CONFIGURATION Requires a Oracle BI data server with the folowwing JDBC property: NQ_SESSION.SELECTPHYSICAL = yes
OPTIONS (Refer to Option descriptions for more information on each option) OBIEE_SQL_PREFIX : This can be set with any valid OBIEE sql prefix. For e.g, set variable EFFECTIVE_DATE='2008-10-01'
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

<%String fromClause;%> <%fromClause=odiRef.getFrom();%> <%java.util.regex.Pattern pat = java.util.regex.Pattern.compile("(\s+)select(\s+)|(\s+)SELECT(\s+)|(\()select(\s+)|(\()SELECT(\s+)");%> <%java.util.regex.Matcher mat = pat.matcher(fromClause);%> <%fromClause=mat.replaceAll("$1$3$5$7select_physical$2$4$6$8");%>
<%=odiRef.getOption("OBIEE_SQL_PREFIX")%> select_physical <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]\t[ALIAS_SEP] [CX_COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "")%> from <%=fromClause%> where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getJoin()%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=odiRef.getHaving()%>

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
